the text is written entirely by a human.', 'document_classification': 'HUMAN_ONLY', 'version': '2025-01-09-base', 'language': 'en', 'pageNumber': 0, 'inputText': 'The spirit of Magellan, the worldwide traveler, is alive and well as Joseph circumnavigates the tip of South America on an expedition passenger ship. He sails through Tierra del Fuego and around Cape Horn on Travelscope\'s latest Chilean adventure. As the ship follows Darwin\'s watery trail, he travels into the Beagle Channel and through "Glaciers Avenue" where the majestic Spain, Romanche, Germany, Italy, France and Holland glaciers seem close enough to touch. Along the way he encounters Elephant Seals, Magellanic Penguins and sea birds aplenty. A highlight of the show is a stop on Isla Del Horno - Horn Island - where Joseph stands at the end of the Americas and visits the memorial to the ancient mariners who lost their lives attempting to make the Cape Horn passage. Episode Duration: 26 minutes and 46 seconds Episode Number: 613 The Daytime Emmy-winning travel series Travelscope- now re-titled JOSEPH ROSENDO\'S TRAVELSCOPE- scales new heights of adventure, natural splendor and cultural richness this season. Host Joseph Rosendo journeys from the California coast to the islands of Hong Kong and to Chile\'s Tierra del Fuego. Along the way, he encounters the heights of natural beauty in the Cariboo-Chilcotin Coast region of British Columbia, celebrates Christmas in Switzerland and circumnavigates the tip of South America. The series\' hallmark remains the rich cultural interchanges between Joseph and the local population. He joins the parade of medieval guilds during Zurich\'s spring festival, shares devotions with a holy man in a rock-hewn church in Lalibela, Ethiopia and explores the mysteries behind the stone figures on Easter Island. Visit the Joseph Rosendo\'s Travelsc... web site WENH-TV Ch. 11 Durham WLED-TV Ch. 48 Littleton WEKW-TV Ch. 18 Keene W50DP-D Ch. 50 Hanover W34DQ-D Ch. 34 Pittsburg Cable and Satellite Channels NHPBS - 11.1 NH Explore - 11.2 NH World - 11.3 NH Create - 11.4 NH Kids - 11.5 Learn More NHPBS Primetime Grid NH Explore Primetime Grid Connections Newsletter (Printable) NHPBS Primetime Grid NH Explore Primetime Grid Connections Newsletter (Printable) Can I watch NHPBS live online? How can I find NHPBS channel(s) on my TV? What\'s the difference between NHPBS and NH EXPLORE (Kids, Create, World?) Where can I find information about Closed Captioning? How can I get NHPBS for free over the air? NHPBS inspires one million Granite Staters each month with engaging and trusted local and national programs on-air, online, in classrooms and in communities. 268 Mast Rd. 'version': '2025-01-09-base', 'language': 'en', 'pageNumber': 0, 'inputText': 'Deals, scams, your money, unemployment— Jeff’s newsletter cuts through the noise. Here are all of the Rossen Reports from this past week. Inflation is still hitting our wallets when it comes to food! The latest Consumer Price Index shows going out to eat, is costing us more than 5% more than this time last year. Watch the video for this story in the player above. Now, fast-food chains are beefing up their value meals, making it easier for you to get more food for less. What does a dollar get you? What about $5? What about $10? Rossen Reports is finding out at different fast-food chains, getting as much food while still staying under the limit. Watch the video above to see the results. Read the full story here. With the Super Bowl less than a couple of weeks away, you can get major savings on televisions. The biggest sales are happening right now through Presidents Day. How can you get major discounts? Read the full story here. An urgent warning is out after a new report says data breaches are up in record numbers. In a new report from the Identity Theft Resource Center, there were 3,205 data breaches in 2023. That\'s a 78% increase from 2022 and an all-time high. What can you do to protect yourself in a data breach? Read the full story here. Robocalls are still on the rise! David emailed Rossen Reports saying he\'s on the "Do Not Call" registry, but he\'s not sure it\'s working. How can he stop robocalls? Let\'s review a few things about the National Do Not Call Registry: It\'s designed to stop unwanted sales and telemarketing calls coming from real, legitimate companies. Scammers (and companies that aren\'t following the law) don\'t pay attention to this list. Even then, it tells these companies NOT to call you but it doesn\'t BLOCK their calls. This registry also doesn\'t stop things like political calls, charitable calls, and informational calls. Read the full story here. Hearst Television participates in various affiliate marketing programs, which means we may get paid commissions on editorially chosen products purchased through our links to retailer sites.'}]
